How to save time typing messages on your iPhone or iPad

Subscribe to the Guardian HERE: http://bitly.com/UvkFpD

Typing text on your mobile can sometimes be quite fiddly - especially when writing long words or phrases such as email addresses. This video shows you how to benefit from a little-used feature in the iOS settings on an Apple iPhone or iPad that allows you to create a shortcut to make longer words appear. This method can also be used to override incorrect suggestions for unusually-spelled words such as surnames and place names which iOS often gets wrong.